SW = On the nominal RIM. (Not referred to the PERMITTED RIMS)



S = Single fitment



SRI = Speed Radius Index - value to be used for calculation of the theoretical tractor speed during European Union homologation and for the interchangeability of different tyre sizes.



For application on hillside, increase the pressure by 0,5 bar.



For dual mounting use the pressure correspondent to the load per each wheel divided by 0,88.



IMPORTANT: The inflation pressure is established considering the application and the load for each tyre.
